resenting Phonological DetailPart I: Segmental Structure and RepresentationsPart II: Syllable, Stress and Sign Part II of Representing Phonological Detail focuses on the latest phonological research on suprasegmental structure and sign language. The first main theme in this volume is syllable structure, touching on phonotactics, syllabification, gemination, syllable weight, diphthongization, and other rules. The other main theme is tone and stress, including issues in data collection, the assignment of primary and secondary stress, resolution of stress clashes, lexical accent, and syntax-tone interaction. The final section is on sign language, with special attention paid to iconicity, phonological processes, and the relation between phonetic and phonological representation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aAkzent. 4aLinguistik. 4aMorphologie. 4aPhonetik. 4aPhonologie. 4aSilbe. 4aVorzeichen. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Phonetics & Phonology.2bisacsh  aLinguistics.  aMorphology.  aPhonetics.  aPhonology.1 aAgostinho, Ana Lívia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBogomolets, Ksenia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButskhrikidze, Marika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalabrese, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChannon, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrasborn, Onno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDresher, B. Elan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoedemans, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/